info.headline: Wind Advisory issued February 26 at 1:38PM PST until February 27 at 8:00AM PST by NWS Eureka
info.description: ...WIND ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 9 PM THIS EVENING TO 8 AM PST MONDAY... * WHAT...South winds 15 to 25 mph with gusts up to 45 mph expected. * WHERE...Coastal Del Norte, Del Norte Interior, Northern Humboldt Coast, Southwestern Humboldt, Northern Humboldt Interior, Southern Humboldt Interior and Northwestern Mendocino Interior Counties. * WHEN...From 9 PM this evening to 8 AM PST Monday. * IMPACTS...Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects. Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may result.
info.instruction: Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.
